{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859003203,"sessionID":"ses_2868e580dffe37hvZB3WUKJzxW","part":{"id":"prt_d7971e118001t5ZnK2N1nrQuBc","messageID":"msg_d7971d4a70012w3pcDc3Q4xMe5","sessionID":"ses_2868e580dffe37hvZB3WUKJzxW","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b0297ce4a46445e68338eb19","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","limit":200},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-007 — K8s Reconciler Controller\n2: \n3: - **AR ID**: AR-007\n4: - **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n5: - **Language**: Go\n6: - **Size**: L\n7: - **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n8: \n9: ## 1. Architecture\n10: \n11: ### 1.1 Overview\n12: \n13: The K8s Reconciler Controller is a Kubernetes controller that watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources and ensures the desired runtime state matches the actual cluster state. It provides declarative management of sandbox runtimes through the Kubernetes API server, enabling native Kubernetes patterns for resource lifecycle management.\n14: \n15: ### 1.2 Component Structure\n16: \n17: ```\n18: pkg/workloadmanager/\n19: ├── controller/\n20: │   ├── controller.go           # Controller framework & reconciliation loop\n21: │   ├── reconciler.go           # Reconciler implementation\n22: │   ├── agentruntime_reconciler.go    # AgentRuntime-specific reconciliation\n23: │   ├── codeinterpreter_reconciler.go # CodeInterpreter-specific reconciliation\n24: │   └── controller_test.go      # Controller tests\n25: ├── informer/\n26: │   ├── factory.go              # Shared informer factory setup\n27: │   └── handlers.go             # Custom event handlers\n28: ├── reconciler/\n29: │   ├── types.go                # Reconciler data structures\n30: │   ├── status.go               # Status update utilities\n31: │   ├── conditions.go           # Condition helpers\n32: │   └── finalizer.go            # Finalizer management\n33: ├── client.go                   # Kubernetes client initialization (existing)\n34: ├── service.go                  # WorkloadManager interface (existing)\n35: ├── server.go                   # HTTP server (existing)\n36: └── types.go                    # Request/Response types (existing)\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ### 1.3 Architecture Diagram\n40: \n41: ```\n42: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n43: │                         Kubernetes API Server                           │\n44: │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐ │\n45: │  │ AgentRuntime    │  │ CodeInterpreter │  │ Pods/Service/ConfigMap  │ │\n46: │  │ (CRD)           │  │ (CRD)           │  │ (Managed Resources)     │ │\n47: │  └────────┬────────┘  └────────┬────────┘  └───────────┬────────────┘ │\n48: │           │                     │                        │              │\n49: └───────────┼─────────────────────┼────────────────────────┼──────────────┘\n50:             │                     │                        │\n51:             ▼                     ▼                        ▼\n52: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n53: │                    K8s Reconciler Controller                            │\n54: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n55: │  │                    SharedInformerFactory                           │ │\n56: │  │  ┌──────────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────────────────────┐ │ │\n57: │  │  │ AgentRuntime Informer│    │ CodeInterpreter Informer        │ │ │\n58: │  │  └──────────┬───────────┘    └───────────────┬──────────────────┘ │ │\n59: │  │             │                                  │                    │ │\n60: │  │             ▼                                  ▼                    │ │\n61: │  │  ┌──────────────────────┐    ┌──────────────────────────────────┐ │ │\n62: │  │  │ AgentRuntime Lister  │    │ CodeInterpreter Lister           │ │ │\n63: │  │  └──────────────────────┘    └──────────────────────────────────┘ │ │\n64: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n65: │                                    │                                      │\n66: │                                    ▼                                      │\n67: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n68: │  │              Reconciliation Loop (WorkQueue)                       │ │\n69: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌──────────┐ │ │\n70: │  │  │  Enqueue    │→ │   Reconcile  │→ │   Update    │→ │  Update  │ │ │\n71: │  │  │  (trigger)  │  │   (compare)  │  │   (diff)    │  │  Status  │ │ │\n72: │  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └──────────┘ │ │\n73: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n74: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n75:                                     │\n76:                                     ▼\n77: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n78: │                     WorkloadManager Service                             │\n79: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n80: │  │  HTTP API Layer (server.go)                                        │ │\n81: │  │  - CRUD operations for AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter                │ │\n82: │  │  - Sandbox lifecycle management                                    │ │\n83: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n84: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n85: ```\n86: \n87: ### 1.4 Reconciliation Flow\n88: \n89: ```\n90:                     ┌─────────────────────┐\n91:                     │  Object Created/    │\n92:                     │  Updated/Deleted    │\n93:                     └──────────┬──────────┘\n94:                                │\n95:                                ▼\n96:                     ┌─────────────────────┐\n97:                     │  Informer Event     │\n98:                     │  (Add/Update/Delete)│\n99:                     └──────────┬──────────┘\n100:                                │\n101:                                ▼\n102:                     ┌─────────────────────┐\n103:                     │  Enqueue with Key   │\n104:                     │  (namespace/name)   │\n105:                     └──────────┬──────────┘\n106:                                │\n107:                                ▼\n108:                     ┌─────────────────────┐\n109:                     │  Get from Lister   │\n110:                     │  (cached object)    │\n111:                     └──────────┬──────────┘\n112:                                │\n113:                                ▼\n114:                     ┌─────────────────────┐\n115:                     │  Reconcile Object   │\n116:                     │                     │\n117:                     │  1. Fetch latest    │\n118:                     │  2. Check deletion  │\n119:                     │  3. Ensure finalizer│\n120:                     │  4. Reconcile spec  │\n121:                     │  5. Update status   │\n122:                     └──────────┬──────────┘\n123:                                │\n124:                                ▼\n125:                     ┌─────────────────────┐\n126:                     │  Update Status     │\n127:                     │  (conditions, gen)  │\n128:                     └─────────────────────┘\n129: ```\n130: \n131: ## 2. Data Structures\n132: \n133: ### 2.1 Controller Types\n134: \n135: ```go\n136: // ControllerConfig holds controller configuration\n137: type ControllerConfig struct {\n138:     // Namespace to watch. Empty means all namespaces.\n139:     Namespace string\n140:     \n141:     // ResyncPeriod is the period to force a full sync\n142:     ResyncPeriod time.Duration\n143:     \n144:     // MaxConcurrentReconciles is the max concurrent reconciliation threads\n145:     MaxConcurrentReconciles int\n146:     \n147:     // Reconciler is the actual reconcile logic implementation\n148:     Reconciler Reconciler\n149:     \n150:     // Client is the Kubernetes clientset\n151:     Client kubernetes.Interface\n152:     \n153:     // Scheme is the API scheme\n154:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n155: }\n156: \n157: // Controller manages the reconciliation loop\n158: type Controller interface {\n159:     // Run starts the controller\n160:     Run(ctx context.Context, workers int) error\n161:     \n162:     // WaitForCacheSync waits for informers to sync\n163:     WaitForCacheSync(ctx context.Context) bool\n164:     \n165:     // GetHandler returns the event handler\n166:     GetHandler() cache.HandlerFuncs\n167: }\n168: ```\n169: \n170: ### 2.2 Reconciler Interface\n171: \n172: ```go\n173: // Reconciler reconciles AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources\n174: type Reconciler interface {\n175:     // ReconcileAgentRuntime reconciles an AgentRuntime resource\n176:     ReconcileAgentRuntime(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)\n177:     \n178:     // ReconcileCodeInterpreter reconciles a CodeInterpreter resource  \n179:     ReconcileCodeInterpreter(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)\n180:     \n181:     // SetupWithManager sets up the controller with a manager\n182:     SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager, options ControllerOptions) error\n183: }\n184: \n185: // AgentRuntimeReconciler reconciles AgentRuntime resources\n186: type AgentRuntimeReconciler struct {\n187:     client     client.Client\n188:     scheme     *runtime.Scheme\n189:     log        logr.Logger\n190:     recorder   record.EventRecorder\n191: }\n192: \n193: // CodeInterpreterReconciler reconciles CodeInterpreter resources\n194: type CodeInterpreterReconciler struct {\n195:     client     client.Client\n196:     scheme     *runtime.Scheme\n197:     log        logr.Logger\n198:     recorder   record.EventRecorder\n199: }\n200: ```\n\n(Showing lines 1-200 of 2002. Use offset=201 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-007 — K8s Reconciler Controller\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-007\n- **Module**: pkg/workloadmanager\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nThe K8s Reconciler Controller is a Kubernetes controller that watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources and ensures the desired runtime state matches the actual cluster state. It provides declarative management of sandbox runtimes through the Kubernetes API server, enabling native Kubernetes patterns for resource lifecycle management.\n\n### 1.2 Component Structure\n\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── controller/\n│   ├── controller.go           # Controller framework & reconciliation loop","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775859003147,"end":1775859003201}}}}
