{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775859145192,"sessionID":"ses_2868e580dffe37hvZB3WUKJzxW","part":{"id":"prt_d79728bf1001i3Yiiw0iWM1YLp","messageID":"msg_d79727d0f001CgaacBTRbXeRgq","sessionID":"ses_2868e580dffe37hvZB3WUKJzxW","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_3dfc63488a5c434d8b2a6914","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-019 — CLI Binary Entry Points (4 Binaries)\n\n- **AR ID**: AR-019\n- **Module**: cmd\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: M\n- **Status**: ST-1 Completed (design.md)\n\n## 1. Architecture\n\n### 1.1 Overview\n\nAgentCube provides four CLI binary entry points for its Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform. Each binary serves a distinct role in the system architecture, communicating via the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group using the generated client-go library.\n\n### 1.2 Binary Overview\n\n| Binary | Purpose | Port | Dependencies |\n|--------|---------|------|--------------|\n| `agentd` | K8s Reconciler Controller | N/A | K8s API Server, etcd |\n| `picod` | Code Execution Daemon | 8080 (configurable) | Local filesystem |\n| `router` | HTTP Session Router | 8080 | Redis/Valkey, WorkloadManager |\n| `workload-manager` | Sandbox Lifecycle Manager | 8080 | K8s API Server, Redis/Valkey |\n\n### 1.3 Component Structure\n\n```\ncmd/\n├── agentd/\n│   ├── main.go                      # Controller entry point\n│   └── ...\n├── picod/\n│   ├── main.go                      # Code execution daemon entry\n│   └── ...\n├── router/\n│   ├── main.go                      # Router entry point\n│   └── ...\n└── workload-manager/\n    ├── main.go                      # Workload manager entry point\n    └── ...\n```\n\n### 1.4 Architecture Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                              AgentCube System                                │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                             │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                        agentd (Controller)                           │   │\n│  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │   │\n│  │  │  Watches: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter CRDs                 │  │   │\n│  │  │  Creates: Pods, Services, ConfigMaps                          │  │   │\n│  │  │  Status Updates: AgentRuntimeStatus, CodeInterpreterStatus    │  │   │\n│  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                 │                                             │\n│                                 │ K8s API                                     │\n│                                 ▼                                             │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                    Kubernetes API Server                             │   │\n│  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────┐   │   │\n│  │  │ AgentRuntime    │  │ CodeInterpreter │  │ Pod/Service/Config │   │   │\n│  │  │ (CRD)          │  │ (CRD)           │  │ (Native resources)│   │   │\n│  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └────────────────────┘   │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                    │                                         │\n├────────────────────────────────────┼────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                    │                                         │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────┴─────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                    workload-manager                                 │   │\n│  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n│  │  │ HTTP API    │  │ Sandbox CRUD │  │ Session Lifecycle       │   │   │\n│  │  │ (Gin)       │  │              │  │                         │   │   │\n│  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                 │                                           │\n│                                 │ Session events                            │\n│                                 ▼                                           │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                    Redis/Valkey (Session Store)                     │   │\n│  │  - Session data (session-routing)                                   │   │\n│  │  - Sandbox state                                                    │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                    │                                         │\n│                                    │ Proxy routing                           │\n│                                    ▼                                         │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                         router                                      │   │\n│  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n│  │  │ Session     │  │ Auth/JWT    │  │ Backend Health Check    │   │   │\n│  │  │ Routing     │  │ Middleware  │  │                          │   │   │\n│  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n│  └──────────────────────────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                 │                                           │\n│                                 │ HTTP Requests                             │\n│                                 ▼                                           │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                      Sandbox Pods                                   │   │\n│  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │   │\n│  │  │ Agent        │  │ Code         │  │ Services                 │   │   │\n│  │  │ Container    │  │ Interpreter  │  │ (NodePort/ClusterIP)    │   │   │\n│  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                    │                                         │\n│                                    │ Optional                                │\n│                                    ▼                                         │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                         picod                                       │   │\n│  │  - Code execution daemon inside sandbox pods                       │   │\n│  │  - File operations, execution                                       │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                                                             │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.5 Data Flow\n\n```\n                                    ┌─────────────────┐\n                                    │   Client Request│\n                                    └────────┬────────┘\n                                             │\n                                             ▼\n                               ┌─────────────────────────┐\n                               │      router             │\n                               │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n                               │  │ Auth Middleware   │  │\n                               │  │ JWT/Token Review  │  │\n                               │  └───────────────────┘  │\n                               │            │            │\n                               │            ▼            │\n                               │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n                               │  │ Session Manager   │  │\n                               │  │ → Redis lookup    │  │\n                               │  └───────────────────┘  │\n                               │            │            │\n                               │            ▼            │\n                               │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n                               │  │ Backend Selector  │  │\n                               │  │ → WorkloadManager │  │\n                               │  └───────────────────┘  │\n                               └───────────┬─────────────┘\n                                           │\n                                           ▼\n                               ┌─────────────────────────┐\n                               │  workload-manager      │\n                               │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n                               │  │ API Handlers      │  │\n                               │  │ GET/POST/DELETE   │  │\n                               │  └───────────────────┘  │\n                               │            │            │\n                               │            ▼            │\n                               │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n                               │  │ Client-go         │  │\n                               │  │ → K8s API         │  │\n                               │  └───────────────────┘  │\n                               └───────────┬─────────────┘\n                                           │\n                                           ▼\n                               ┌─────────────────────────┐\n                               │  Kubernetes API Server  │\n                               │  - Create AgentRuntime │\n                               │  - Create Pod/Service  │\n                               └───────────┬─────────────┘\n                                           │\n                                           ▼\n                               ┌─────────────────────────┐\n                               │      agentd             │\n                               │  ┌───────────────────┐  │\n                               │  │ Controller        │  │\n                               │  │ → Reconcile loop  │  │\n                               │  └───────────────────┘  │\n                               └─────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## 2. Binary Specifications\n\n### 2.1 agentd — Kubernetes Controller\n\n**Entry Point**: `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n\nThe agentd binary runs as a Kubernetes controller using controller-runtime. It watches `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` custom resources and ensures the desired runtime state matches the actual cluster state.\n\n#### Command-Line Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--metrics-bind-address` | string | \"0\" | Metrics server bind address (0 = disabled) |\n| `--health-probe-bind-address` | string | \"0\" | Health probe bind address |\n| `--leader-elect` | bool | false | Enable leader election |\n| `--leader-elect-lease-duration` | duration | 15s | Leader election lease duration |\n| `--leader-elect-renew-deadline` | duration | 10s | Leader election renew deadline |\n| `--leader-elect-retry-period` | duration | 5s | Leader election retry period |\n\n#### Configuration\n\n```go\ntype AgentdConfig struct {\n    // Metrics server configuration\n    MetricsBindAddress string\n    \n    // Health probe configuration  \n    HealthProbeBindAddress string\n    \n    // Leader election\n    LeaderElect        bool\n    LeaseDuration      time.Duration\n    RenewDeadline      time.Duration\n    RetryPeriod        time.Duration\n    \n    // Namespace to watch (empty = all namespaces)\n    WatchNamespace     string\n    \n    // Sync period for full reconciliation\n    SyncPeriod         time.Duration\n    \n    // Max concurrent reconciles\n    MaxConcurrentReconciles int\n}\n```\n\n#### Dependencies\n\n- `pkg/agentd/` — Controller implementation\n- `pkg/client/informers/` — Generated informers\n- `pkg/client/listers/` — Generated listers\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` — API types\n\n### 2.2 picod — Code Execution Daemon\n\n**Entry Point**: `cmd/picod/main.go`\n\nThe picod binary runs inside sandbox pods as a code execution daemon, providing file operations and code execution capabilities.\n\n#### Command-Line Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--port` | int | 8080 | Server listen port |\n| `--workspace` | string | \"\" | Root directory for file operations (default: cwd) |\n| `--auth-mode` | string | \"picod\" | Authentication mode: picod, none |\n| `--session-timeout` | duration | 15m | Session timeout |\n| `--max-session-duration` | duration | 8h | Maximum session duration |\n\n#### Configuration\n\n```go\ntype PicoDConfig struct {\n    Port              int\n    Workspace         string\n    AuthMode          string\n    SessionTimeout    time.Duration\n    MaxSessionDuration time.Duration\n}\n```\n\n#### API Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | `/health` | Health check |\n| POST | `/execute` | Execute code |\n| GET | `/files/*path` | Read file |\n| PUT | `/files/*path` | Write file |\n| DELETE | `/files/*path` | Delete file |\n\n#### Dependencies\n\n- `pkg/picod/` — Server implementation\n\n### 2.3 router — HTTP Session Router\n\n**Entry Point**: `cmd/router/main.go`\n\nThe router binary provides HTTP routing with session management, authentication, and proxy capabilities. It routes incoming requests to the appropriate sandbox backend based on session affinity.\n\n#### Command-Line Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--listen-address` | string | \":8080\" | Server listen address |\n| `--workload-manager-url` | string | \"\" | WorkloadManager backend URL (required) |\n| `--backend-timeout` | duration | 30s | Backend request timeout |\n| `--idle-timeout` | duration | 60s | Idle connection timeout |\n| `--health-check-interval` | duration | 10s | Health check interval |\n| `--health-check-timeout` | duration | 5s | Health check timeout |\n| `--max-conns-per-backend` | int | 100 | Max connections per backend |\n| `--rate-limit-enabled` | bool | false | Enable rate limiting |\n| `--rate-limit-rps` | int | 10 | Rate limit RPS |\n| `--auth-enabled` | bool | false | Enable authentication |\n| `--auth-token` | string | \"\" | Bearer token for auth |\n| `--session-enabled` | bool | false | Enable session management |\n| `--session-timeout` | duration | 30m | Session timeout |\n| `--session-cookie-name` | string | \"AGENTSESSIONID\" | Session cookie name |\n| `--jwt-enabled` | bool | false | Enable JWT authentication |\n| `--jwt-secret` | string | \"\" | JWT secret for HS256 |\n| `--jwt-private-key-path` | string | \"\" | Path to RS256 private key |\n| `--jwt-public-key-path` | string | \"\" | Path to RS256 public key |\n\n#### Configuration\n\n```go\ntype RouterConfig struct {\n    ListenAddress       string\n    WorkloadManagerURL string\n    \n    // Backend\n    BackendTimeout      time.Duration\n    IdleTimeout         time.Duration\n    HealthCheckInterval time.Duration\n    HealthCheckTimeout  time.Duration\n    MaxConnsPerBackend  int\n    \n    // Rate limiting\n    RateLimitEnabled    bool\n    RateLimitRPS        int\n    \n    // Auth\n    AuthEnabled         bool\n    AuthToken           string\n    \n    // Session management\n    SessionEnabled         bool\n    SessionTimeout         time.Duration\n    SessionCookieName      string\n    SessionMaxActive       int\n    SessionCookieSecure    bool\n    SessionCookieHTTPOnly  bool\n    SessionCookieDomain    string\n    SessionCleanupInterval time.Duration\n    \n    // JWT\n    JWTEnabled           bool\n    JWTAlgorithm         string\n    JWTSecret            string\n    JWTPrivateKeyPath    string\n    JWTPublicKeyPath     string\n    JWTIssuer            string\n    JWTAudience          []string\n    JWTExpiration        time.Duration\n    JWTRefreshExpiration time.Duration\n    JWTClockSkew         time.Duration\n    JWTAllowQueryParam   bool\n}\n```\n\n#### Dependencies\n\n- `pkg/router/` — Router implementation\n- `pkg/store/` — Session store (Redis/Valkey)\n- `pkg/client/clientset/` — Generated client-go\n\n### 2.4 workload-manager — Sandbox Lifecycle Manager\n\n**Entry Point**: `cmd/workload-manager/main.go`\n\nThe workload-manager binary provides REST APIs for sandbox lifecycle management. It creates and manages AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources in Kubernetes.\n\n#### Command-Line Flags\n\n| Flag | Type | Default | Description |\n|------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `--listen-address` | string | \":8080\" | Server listen address |\n| `--store-type` | string | \"redis\" | Store type: redis, valkey |\n| `--store-address` | string | \"localhost:6379\" | Store address |\n| `--store-password` | string | \"\" | Store password |\n| `--store-db` | int | 0 | Store database number |\n| `--namespace` | string | \"default\" | Default Kubernetes namespace |\n| `--session-timeout` | duration | 15m | Default session timeout |\n| `--max-session-duration` | duration | 8h | Default max session duration |\n| `--gc-interval` | duration | 5m | Garbage collection interval |\n| `--gc-worker-count` | int | 5 | GC worker count |\n\n#### Configuration\n\n```go\ntype WorkloadManagerConfig struct {\n    // Server\n    ListenAddress string\n    \n    // Store (Redis/Valkey)\n    StoreType    string\n    StoreAddress string\n    StorePassword string\n    StoreDB      int\n    \n    // Kubernetes\n    Namespace string\n    \n    // Session defaults\n    SessionTimeout       time.Duration\n    MaxSessionDuration   time.Duration\n    \n    // Garbage collection\n    GCInterval     time.Duration\n    GCWorkerCount  int\n    \n    // Webhook configuration (optional)\n    Webhooks []WebhookConfig\n}\n\ntype WebhookConfig struct {\n    URL        string\n    Timeout    int\n    RetryCount int\n}\n```\n\n#### API Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Description |\n|--------|------|-------------|\n| GET | `/health` | Health check |\n| POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` | Create sandbox |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes` | List sandboxes |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}` | Get sandbox |\n| DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/sandboxes/{name}` | Delete sandbox |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | List AgentRuntimes |\n| POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes` | Create AgentRuntime |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Get AgentRuntime |\n| DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agentruntimes/{name}` | Delete AgentRuntime |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | List CodeInterpreters |\n| POST | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters` | Create CodeInterpreter |\n| GET | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Get CodeInterpreter |\n| DELETE | `/api/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/codeinterpreters/{name}` | Delete CodeInterpreter |\n\n#### Dependencies\n\n- `pkg/workloadmanager/` — Manager implementation\n- `pkg/store/` — Session store (Redis/Valkey)\n- `pkg/client/clientset/` — Generated client-go\n\n## 3. API Contracts\n\n### 3.1 AgentRuntime (CRD)\n\n**API Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`  \n**Version**: `v1alpha1`  \n**Plural**: `agentruntimes`  \n**Short Name**: `ar`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: AgentRuntime\nmetadata:\n  name: my-agent\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n  sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n  targetPorts:\n    - port: 8080\n      protocol: HTTP\n      name: http\n  podTemplate:\n    spec:\n      containers:\n        - name: agent\n          image: my-agent:latest\n          resources:\n            limits:\n              cpu: \"1\"\n              memory: \"1Gi\"\nstatus:\n  phase: Running\n  endpoint: \"http://my-agent.default.sandbox.example.com\"\n  conditions:\n    - type: Ready\n      status: \"True\"\n      lastTransitionTime: \"2024-01-01T00:00:00Z\"\n```\n\n### 3.2 CodeInterpreter (CRD)\n\n**API Group**: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`  \n**Version**: `v1alpha1`  \n**Plural**: `codeinterpreters`  \n**Short Name**: `ci`\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\nkind: CodeInterpreter\nmetadata:\n  name: my-interpreter\n  namespace: default\nspec:\n  authMode: picod\n  maxSessionDuration: \"8h\"\n  sessionTimeout: \"15m\"\n  template:\n    image: python:3.11\n    command: [\"python\", \"-m\", \"picod\"]\n  warmPoolSize: 0\nstatus:\n  phase: Running\n  endpoint: \"http://my-interpreter.default.sandbox.example.com\"\n  ready: true\n```\n\n### 3.3 Client-Go Library Usage\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"k8s.io/client-go/tools/clientcmd\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned\"\n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/client/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n)\n\nconfig, _ := clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags(\"\", \"\")\nclientset, _ := versioned.NewForConfig(config)\n\n// Create AgentRuntime\narClient := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\")\nagentRuntime := &v1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n    // ... spec\n}\nresult, err := arClient.Create(ctx, agentRuntime, metav1.CreateOptions{})\n\n// List CodeInterpreters\nciClient := clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(\"default\")\nlist, err := ciClient.List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{})\n```\n\n## 4. Error Handling\n\n### 4.1 Error Codes\n\n| Code | Name | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| 400 | BadRequest | Invalid request format or parameters |\n| 401 | Unauthorized | Authentication failed |\n| 403 | Forbidden | Insufficient permissions |\n| 404 | NotFound | Resource not found |\n| 409 | Conflict | Resource already exists |\n| 422 | UnprocessableEntity | Validation failed |\n| 429 | TooManyRequests | Rate limit exceeded |\n| 500 | InternalServerError | Internal server error |\n| 502 | BadGateway | Upstream unavailable |\n| 503 | ServiceUnavailable | Service temporarily unavailable |\n| 504 | GatewayTimeout | Upstream timeout |\n\n### 4.2 Error Response Format\n\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": 404,\n    \"message\": \"Resource not found\",\n    \"details\": {\n      \"resource\": \"AgentRuntime\",\n      \"name\": \"my-agent\",\n      \"namespace\": \"default\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 4.3 Common Errors\n\n| Error | HTTP Code | Retry | Resolution |\n|-------|-----------|-------|------------|\n| SandboxNotFound | 404 | No | Check name/namespace |\n| DeletionFailed | 500 | Yes | Check K8s cluster state |\n| StaleFinalizer | 500 | No | Manual cleanup required |\n| OrphanedResource | 500 | Yes | Force delete |\n| ResourceNotFound | 404 | No | Resource already deleted |\n\n## 5. Testing Strategy\n\n### 5.1 Unit Tests\n\nEach binary should have unit tests for:\n- Configuration parsing\n- Flag handling\n- Error cases\n\n```go\n// Example: router configuration test\nfunc TestRouterConfig(t *testing.T) {\n    tests := []struct {\n        name    string\n        flags   []string\n        wantErr bool\n    }{\n        {\n            name:    \"valid config with required flags\",\n            flags:   []string{\"--workload-manager-url\", \"http://localhost:8080\"},\n            wantErr: false,\n        },\n        {\n            name:    \"missing required flag\",\n            flags:   []string{},\n            wantErr: true,\n        },\n    }\n    \n    for _, tt := range tests {\n        t.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n            // Test configuration parsing\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### 5.2 Integration Tests\n\n- End-to-end binary startup tests\n- K8s client integration tests (requires test cluster)\n- Store integration tests (requires Redis/Valkey)\n\n### 5.3 Build Verification\n\n```bash\n# Build all binaries\ngo build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd\ngo build -o bin/picod ./cmd/picod\ngo build -o bin/router ./cmd/router\ngo build -o bin/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager\n\n# Verify binaries exist and are executable\nls -la bin/\n```\n\n## 6. Dependencies\n\n### 6.1 Go Module Dependencies\n\n```\ngithub.com/volcano-sh/agentcube          # Main module\n  ├── k8s.io/api                          # K8s API types\n  ├── k8s.io/apimachinery                 # K8s utilities\n  ├── k8s.io/client-go                   # K8s client\n  ├── k8s.io/klog/v2                     # Logging\n  ├── k8s.io/controller-runtime          # Controller framework\n  ├── github.com/gin-gonic/gin            # HTTP framework\n  ├── github.com/redis/go-redis/v9        # Redis client\n  ├── github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go      # Valkey client\n  ├── github.com/prometheus/client_golang # Metrics\n  └── github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5       # JWT support\n```\n\n### 6.2 External Dependencies\n\n| Component | Requirement | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|-------------|\n| Kubernetes | ≥1.24 | K8s API server |\n| Redis/Valkey | ≥6.0 | Session store |\n| Docker | Optional | For building agent images |\n\n## 7. Configuration Precedence\n\nConfiguration is loaded in the following order (later overrides earlier):\n\n1. Default values (hardcoded)\n2. Environment variables (`AGENTCUBE_*`)\n3. Config file (`/etc/agentcube/config.yaml`)\n4. Command-line flags\n\n### 7.1 Environment Variables\n\n| Variable | Binary | Description |\n|----------|--------|-------------|\n| `AGENTCUBE_KUBECONFIG` | all | Path to kubeconfig |\n| `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | all | Default namespace |\n| `AGENTD_METRICS_ADDR` | agentd | Metrics address |\n| `ROUTER_WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | router | Backend URL |\n| `ROUTER_STORE_ADDRESS` | router | Redis/Valkey address |\n| `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_STORE_ADDRESS` | workload-manager | Store address |\n| `PICOD_WORKSPACE` | picod | Workspace directory |\n\n### 7.2 Config File Format\n\n```yaml\n# /etc/agentcube/config.yaml\napiVersion: v1\nkind: AgentCubeConfig\nmetadata:\n  name: agentcube\nspec:\n  namespace: default\n  session:\n    timeout: 15m\n    maxDuration: 8h\n  store:\n    type: redis\n    address: localhost:6379\n    password: \"\"\n  router:\n    listenAddress: \":8080\"\n    workloadManagerURL: \"http://localhost:8081\"\n  workloadManager:\n    listenAddress: \":8081\"\n```\n\n## 8. Deployment\n\n### 8.1 Docker Images\n\nEach binary is packaged as a separate Docker image:\n\n```dockerfile\n# For agentd, router, workload-manager\nFROM golang:1.24-alpine AS builder\nWORKDIR /build\nCOPY go.mod go.sum ./\nRUN go mod download\nCOPY . .\nRUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build -o /agentd ./cmd/agentd\n\nFROM alpine:3.19\nRUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\nCOPY --from=builder /agentd /agentd\nENTRYPOINT [\"/agentd\"]\n```\n\n### 8.2 Kubernetes Deployment\n\nThe system can be deployed using Helm:\n\n```yaml\n# values.yaml\nagentd:\n  enabled: true\n  replicas: 1\n  \nrouter:\n  enabled: true\n  replicas: 2\n  service:\n    type: NodePort\n    port: 80\n    \nworkloadManager:\n  enabled: true\n  replicas: 2\n  \npicod:\n  enabled: true  # Deployed as sidecar in sandbox pods\n```","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/cmd/picod/main.go\">\nERROR [24:39] not enough arguments in call to picod.NewServer\n\thave (*picod.Config)\n\twant (*picod.Config, *picod.AuthConfig)\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspac